[30;1m1069 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m1070 | [0m[35m    Fit `OLS Model <https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ordinary_least_squares>`_ based on observations of[0m
[30;1m1071 | [0m[35m    variables(s) X and the dependant variable y across a rolling window with fixed number of observa[0m
[30;1m1072 | [0m[35m    The parameters of each rolling window are stored at the end of each window.[0m
[30;1m1073 | [0m[35m    If X and y are not aligned, only use the intersection of dates/times.[0m
[30;1m1074 | [0m[35m[0m
[30;1m1075 | [0m[35m    **Examples**[0m

[30;1m208 | [0m[35m<p>where <span class="math notranslate nohighlight">\(X_t\)</span> is the asset price at time <span [0m
[30;1m209 | [0m[35m<p><em>Absolute</em></p>[0m
[30;1m210 | [0m[35m<p>Compute asset price series from absolute returns:</p>[0m
[30;1m211 | [0m[35m<p><span class="math notranslate nohighlight">\(Y_t = X_{t-1} + Y_{t-1}\)</span></p>[0m
